This article is a transcript of a speech given by the Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, on January 6th, 2022. She reflects on the events of January 6th, 2021, when the U.S. Capitol was breached by extremists, and emphasizes the importance of defending democracy. Harris discusses the fragility and strength of democracy and urges the American people to be vigilant in protecting it. She also calls for the passage of voting rights bills and emphasizes the role of the people in securing and strengthening democracy. The speech concludes with the introduction of President Joe Biden.